				<h3 id="post-183"><a href="http://gondwanaland.com/mlog/2005/09/26/against-xenophobia/" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent Link to Against xenophobia"><span class='p-name'>Against xenophobia</span></a></h3>
				<small>Monday, September 26th, 2005</small>

				<div class="entry">
					<div class='e-content'><p>Three cheers for <a href="http://econlog.econlib.org/archives/2005/09/immigration.html">Arnold Kling</a>:</p>
<blockquote><p>
&#8220;Where would you prefer that people be poor?&#8221; That is, do we want to insist that poor Hispanics should remain in their native countries, because we want to make our own national statistics on health insurance coverage and poverty look better?<br />
&#8230;<br />
In my view, economists have to be relatively favorable toward immigration, just as we have to be relatively favorable to free trade in general. It&#8217;s our job to lean against xenophobia.</p></blockquote>
<p>But does Kling realize that <a href="http://gondwanaland.com/mlog/2005/09/10/open-immigration-destroy-capitalism/">immigration will destroy the market system</a> (not)?</p>
</div>				</div>

